Youssouf Mbodou Mbami is the chief of the Canton of Bol and presides over a large swathe of Lake Chad, an area where many young people have been recruited or forced to join terrorist groups, such as Boko Haram.Â 

Daniel Dickinson of UN News travelled with Youssouf Mbodou Mbami to the island of Ngomiron Doumou where up to 300 men, women and children were abducted at gunpoint by Boko Haram fighters in 2015...

